  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (v0.5 synthetic)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The hemolysis scalar transport model employs the power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger (GW) correlation, whose derivation assumes a linear superposition of damage contributions across Lagrangian fluid parcels — an assumption stated in the model narrative as 'broadly applicable to turbomachinery flows'. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
